SIMPLE: cerin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cerin
<hw>Ce"rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>cera</ets> wax
+ <ets>-in</ets>: cf. L. <ets>cerinus</ets> wax-colored.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A waxy substance extracted by
alcohol or ether from cork; sometimes applied also to the portion of
beeswax which is soluble in alcohol.</def> <rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A variety of the mineral
<xex>allanite</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerinthian</ent>⟦br⟧
